author: Inside Edition
description: Anna Kepner's ex-boyfriend, Joshua Tew, spoke with Inside Edition following her funeral at a church outside Orlando, Florida. Kepner, 18, was found dead on a Carnival cruise ship. Tew says that Kepner was so afraid of her stepbrother that she often slept over at her friends' home. The 16-year-old stepbrother is under suspicion for Kepner's death. Tew says the 16-year-old had sexually harassed Kepner. The FBI is investigating Kepner's death because it happened in international waters.
title: Anna Kepner's Ex-Boyfriend Says Her Stepbrother Sexually Harassed Her

author: Inside Edition
description: It's estimated that 82 million people are going to be traveling by road and air this Thanksgiving. 6 million people will travel by air, that's up 1.6 million from last year, setting a new record. Travelers can expect some travel chaos. Some people are taking off the entire week from work for Thanksgiving, turning it into a 10-day holiday. The busiest travel day of the year is no longer the Wednesday before Thanksgiving. It will be the Sunday after the holiday when most people are returning home.
title: This Year's Thanksgiving Expected To Break Travel Records

author: Inside Edition
description: Democratic members of Congress say they fear their lives after President Donald Trump branded them as "traitors" and "seditious behavior" punishable by "death." Michigan Senator Elissa Slotkin is one of six Democrats targeted by Trump after they made a video reminding members of the military they have the right to refuse to obey illegal orders. Trump doubled down on his comments in a radio interview Friday. Now, lawmakers on both sides of the aisle are in uproar.
title: Uproar After Trump Calls Democrats in Congress 'Traitors'

author: Inside Edition
description: The cast of "Everybody Loves Raymond" came together to celebrate nearly three decades since the show first premiered on CBS. The beloved American sitcom, which ran from 1996-2005, followed the life of sports writer Ray Barone, played by Ray Romano, and his close-knit quirky family as they tripped over one another amid life's outrageous moments. In one emotional moment from the reunion, Romano choked up remembering the late Doris Roberts, who plays his overbearing mom, Marie, on the show.
title: Cast Of 'Everybody Loves Raymond' Reunites For 30-Year Anniversary

author: Inside Edition
description: A masked man holding an antenna up to a house with the goal of stealing the code from the car's key fob inside. A device was tucked in his pants capturing the information. The man was able to unlock the vehicle, start the ignition and take off. In another incident, a man could be seen pacing along the side of a house holding an antenna. In the distance, was an accomplice and they stole the truck. Inside Edition has tips to protect yourself from this new crime wave of high tech auto theft.
title: Tips On How To Protect Yourself From High Tech Auto Theft

author: Inside Edition
description: A baby great-horned owl is healing after getting stuck in an unusual situation. The two-pound animal was found in a concrete mixer at a construction site. Staff at Best Friends Animal Society in Kanab, Utah, say they have never seen a case like this in their 40 years. The delicate cleaning process for the baby requires anesthesia, steady hands, and lots of patience. After the bird is healed, it will be released back into the wild. Inside Edition Digital has more.
title: Animal Sanctuary Saves Owl Who Fell In Concrete Mixer

author: Inside Edition
description: A woman who worked on New Jersey Republican congressman Jeff Van Drew's staff told police she was attacked by three men who hate President Donald Trump. Images show her body covered with slashed across her body. The woman has been identified as 26-year-old Natalie Greene.  Now, police say it was all a hoax, and that Greene paid $500 for a body artist to cut her with a scalpel.
title: Former GOP Staffer Accused Of Anti-Trump Attack Hoax #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Former presidents George W. Bush, Joe Biden and their wives Laura and Dr. Jill were in the front pew at Dick Cheney's funeral. Former vice presidents Al Gore, Dan Quayle, Kamala Harris and Mike Pence were also there.
title: Trump And Vance Not Invited To Cheney Funeral #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Anna Kepner's funeral took place in Orlando Thursday. Inside Edition was told there is tension among family members and some have been told they were not welcome to the funeral.
title: Allegations Surface In Cruise Ship Death Of Teen Cheerleader #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A masked man dropped off a holiday note at a doorstep with a threatening message before blowing a kiss to the camera. Video from another neighbor shows two masked men, one with a knife strapped to his waist, leaving a frightening Christmas card in a planter. The cards and notes that were left at multiple homes along a street in Yucaipa, California, look cheerful on the outside but inside, they contain disturbing messages about Nazis.
title: Masked Men Leave Disturbing Holiday Cards On Neighborhood Doorsteps
